14 WHEREAS, Mrs. Jones is a highly decorated veteran and a recipient of numerous awards
15 and commendations for her service and dedication to improving federal operations; and
16 WHEREAS, only those with great strength, discipline, and a firm resolve achieve positions
17 of such status, and Mrs. Jones has brought great credit to herself, her family, this state, and
18 this nation through her outstanding performance and dedication; and
19 WHEREAS, her selfless service stands as a shining tribute to the strength of human spirit and
20 willpower, and it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of
21 this remarkable and distinguished American be appropriately recognized.
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
23 the members of this body recognize and commend Carol Renee Jones for her 45 years of
24 efficient, effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to the State of Georgia and this
25 nation as well as extend the most sincere best wishes for continued health and success.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
27 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Carol
28 Renee Jones.
